definition.value: A glycosyl alditol consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and D-glucitol joined in sequence by (1->3) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A D-idofuranose that has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.
A disaccharide phosphate consisting of 6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannopyranose and D-mannopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.

A glycosyl alditol derivative consisting of D-galactopyranose, 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactitol residues joined in sequence by (1->4) and (1->3) glycosidic bonds.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of a beta-D-mannopyranose residue and two 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-3-O-sulfo-alpha-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glucotriose that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 6 have each been converted into the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranosyl derivatives.
A trisaccharide that is beta-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 have each been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
A glycsyl glycoside derivative that is 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy group has been converted into the corresponding beta-D-galactopyranoside.
A trisaccharide that is lactose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
A disaccharide that is alpha-L-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been converted into the corresponding alpha-L-fucopyranoside
A glucotriose that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 6 have each been converted into the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
